# ERP Export-Utility PDF Standard

## Phase
ERP PDF EXPORT.1 — Arabic Vector PDF via bidi-shaper + Noto Sans Arabic (2026-07-23)

---

## The Problem This Standard Solves

jsPDF's built-in Helvetica font has **no Arabic glyphs**. Two previous broken approaches and why they fail:

| Approach | Problem |
|---|---|
| jsPDF with Helvetica + Arabic text | Every Arabic letter renders in isolation form — disconnected, unreadable. Characters show as `þÎþèþô` garbled symbols. |
| html2canvas → image embedded in jsPDF | File sizes 10–20 MB for a 2-page list. Text is not selectable, blurry when zoomed, non-searchable. |

---

## Correct Approach — REQUIRED for All New Code

Use **`bidi-shaper` + embedded `Noto Sans Arabic` TTF** to produce proper vector PDFs:

1. **`bidi-shaper/jspdf`** — zero-dependency plugin that implements the full Unicode Bidirectional Algorithm (UAX #9) and Arabic contextual shaping (connecting letters, lam-alef ligatures). Install once on `jsPDF.API`.
2. **Noto Sans Arabic TTF** — font file at `public/fonts/noto-sans-arabic-400.ttf` (192 KB, self-hosted). Contains Arabic + Latin glyphs including Arabic Presentation Forms B (U+FB50–U+FEFF) which bidi-shaper targets.
3. **Detection** — `exportDataHasArabic()` scans title, subtitle, and all cell values. Only registers the font + switches body font when Arabic is actually present (no overhead for Latin-only exports).

### Result
- Vector PDF — text is selectable, searchable, copy-pasteable
- Correct Arabic: connected glyphs, proper lam-alef ligatures, RTL direction
- Latin text in the same table renders normally (Noto Sans Arabic has full Latin coverage)
- File size < 300 KB regardless of row count

---

## Implementation Pattern

### Client-side download (`src/lib/export/pdf.ts`)

```typescript
import { installJsPdfShaper } from "bidi-shaper/jspdf";

// Install once at module load — hooks into every doc.text() call automatically
installJsPdfShaper(jsPDF.API as Parameters<typeof installJsPdfShaper>[0]);

// Module-level font cache — fetched once per browser session
let _arabicFontData: string | null = null;

async function loadArabicFont(): Promise<string | null> {
  if (_arabicFontData) return _arabicFontData;
  const res = await fetch("/fonts/noto-sans-arabic-400.ttf");
  if (!res.ok) return null;
  const buf = await res.arrayBuffer();
  const bytes = new Uint8Array(buf);
  const CHUNK = 0x8000;
  const parts: string[] = [];
  for (let i = 0; i < bytes.length; i += CHUNK) {
    parts.push(String.fromCharCode(...bytes.subarray(i, i + CHUNK)));
  }
  return (_arabicFontData = parts.join(""));
}

async function registerArabicFont(doc: jsPDF): Promise<boolean> {
  const data = await loadArabicFont();
  if (!data) return false;
  doc.addFileToVFS("NotoSansArabic.ttf", data);
  doc.addFont("NotoSansArabic.ttf", "NotoSansArabic", "normal");
  return true;
}

// In exportToPDF():
const hasArabic = exportDataHasArabic(options);
let bodyFont = "helvetica";
if (hasArabic) {
  const ok = await registerArabicFont(doc);
  if (ok) bodyFont = "NotoSansArabic";
}

// Pass to autoTable:
autoTable(doc, {
  styles: { font: bodyFont },
  headStyles: { font: "helvetica" }, // headers are always Latin
  // ...
});
```

### Server-side attachment (`src/server/actions/dms/expiry-reminders.ts`)

For server actions, read the font from the filesystem instead of `fetch()`:

```typescript
const { installJsPdfShaper } = await import("bidi-shaper/jspdf");
installJsPdfShaper((jsPDF as { API: ... }).API);

const fs = await import("fs");
const path = await import("path");
const fontBuffer = fs.readFileSync(
  path.join(process.cwd(), "public", "fonts", "noto-sans-arabic-400.ttf")
);
const CHUNK = 0x8000;
const parts: string[] = [];
for (let i = 0; i < fontBuffer.length; i += CHUNK) {
  parts.push(String.fromCharCode(...fontBuffer.subarray(i, i + CHUNK)));
}
doc.addFileToVFS("NotoSansArabic.ttf", parts.join(""));
doc.addFont("NotoSansArabic.ttf", "NotoSansArabic", "normal");
```

