## Rules

### Rule 1 — NEVER use html2canvas for PDF table exports

`html2canvas` produces image-based PDFs. Image PDFs are:
- Not selectable / not searchable
- Blurry at high zoom
- 10–20 MB for a 2-page list (vs < 300 KB for vector)
- Unacceptable for a production ERP

```typescript
// ❌ FORBIDDEN — image PDF
const canvas = await html2canvas(container);
doc.addImage(canvas.toDataURL("image/png"), ...);

// ❌ FORBIDDEN — even with JPEG (still an image)
doc.addImage(canvas.toDataURL("image/jpeg", 0.8), ...);
```

### Rule 2 — ALWAYS use bidi-shaper for any new PDF that may contain Arabic

If you create a new PDF export function anywhere in the codebase and the data could contain Arabic (employee names, document titles, location names, etc.), you MUST:
1. Import and install `installJsPdfShaper`
2. Load and register `NotoSansArabic` font
3. Pass `font: "NotoSansArabic"` to autoTable body styles

### Rule 3 — jsPDF `addFileToVFS` expects a binary string, NOT base64

```typescript
// ✓ Correct — binary string via String.fromCharCode
const bytes = new Uint8Array(arrayBuffer);
const parts: string[] = [];
for (let i = 0; i < bytes.length; i += 0x8000) {
  parts.push(String.fromCharCode(...bytes.subarray(i, i + 0x8000)));
}
doc.addFileToVFS("MyFont.ttf", parts.join(""));

// ❌ Wrong — base64 string
doc.addFileToVFS("MyFont.ttf", btoa(rawString));
```

### Rule 4 — Keep header rows in `helvetica`

Table header labels are always in English. Use `helvetica` for `headStyles.font` to keep them crisp even when the body uses `NotoSansArabic`.

```typescript
autoTable(doc, {
  styles:     { font: bodyFont },          // NotoSansArabic for body cells
  headStyles: { font: "helvetica" },       // Helvetica for header labels
});
```

### Rule 5 — Module-level font cache is mandatory

Loading the 192 KB TTF from disk/network on every export is wasteful. The module-level `_arabicFontData` cache pattern (see Implementation Pattern above) must be used. The font is loaded once per browser session / server worker lifecycle.

### Rule 6 — Arabic detection must cover title AND cell values

```typescript
function exportDataHasArabic<T>(options: ERPExportOptions<T>): boolean {
  if (containsArabic(options.title ?? "")) return true;
  if (containsArabic(options.subtitle ?? "")) return true;   // ← include subtitle
  return options.data.some((row) =>
    options.columns.some((col) => {
      const val = getColumnValue(row, col);
      return typeof val === "string" && containsArabic(val);
    })
  );
}
```

